[5] USA (Texas)
Date: Sun 16 Jun 2013
Source: HealthCare Daily [edited]
http://healthcare.dmagazine.com/2013/06/16/officials-report-second-case-of-measles-in-dallas-county/


A 2nd case of measles has been confirmed in Dallas County [Texas], according to CBS DFW [Dallas-Fort Worth]. A 14-year-old child who had been fully immunized contracted the disease after reportedly being in contact with the person who contracted the 1st case of measles last month [May 2013].

Dallas County Health and Human Services is warning doctors and health care providers to consider the rare disease when patients come in with similar symptoms, such as runny nose, fever, red and watery eyes, cough, or signs of rash all over the body.

More than 1000 cases of measles have been reported in the United Kingdom. In the US, outbreaks have occurred in New York and North Carolina. This year, 2 cases have been confirmed in Denton County [Texas].

[Byline: Aimee Pass]

