[6] Australia (Queensland)
Date: Fri 21 Jun 2013
Source: ABC News 24 [edited]
http://www.abc.net.au/news/2013-06-21/second-cairns-measles-case-sparks-vaccination-warning/4770876


Cairns residents are being warned they may still be at risk of measles, after the detection of a 2nd case linked to a local cinema in the far north Queensland city. A man in his 20s was diagnosed earlier this month and had visited the cinemas at the Cairns Central Shopping Centre. The Director of Tropical Public Health Services, Dr Richard Gair, says a teenage girl who had visited the cinema on the same day as the man has been confirmed as having the disease. Dr Gair says the girl was not vaccinated.

He says anyone who attended the shopping centre on [31 May 2013] should be vigilant. "If they get any measles symptoms and they get a rash, if they're not immune to measles, if they haven't been vaccinated against measles or had measles in the past, they should contact their GP," he said. "[But] maybe not go along to the surgery, because if they go along to the surgery and they've got measles they might infect other people."

[Byline: Kirsty Nancarrow]

